{
  "doc_id": "26090",
  "text": "Several studies investigated the use of MIDO as a means to repress M1 microglial activation and provide neuroprotection [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Therefore, we used MIDO as a positive control and verified its ability to inhibit microglial polarisation into the anti-inflammatory M2 type. The findings of our study indicated that betaine exerted comparable anti-inflammatory effects to those of MIDO, which are in line with the results of previous studies [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
